    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are positioned for a high-ceiling outing today, headlined by **Gunnar Henderson**, who earns our premier spot with an elite 83.29 score. Facing a favorable matchup against Bello, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits significantly from the hitter-friendly park and his locked-in leadoff status, which provides the volume needed for elite category production. He is joined at the top of our output projections by **Kyle Tucker** (73.60) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (69.24). **Kyle Tucker** remains a must-start due to his superior xwOBA metrics, while **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** capitalizes on a high-value #3 order spot, effectively navigating a neutral matchup against Williams. **Nasim Nunez** also warrants attention; despite his lower base projection, his high sprint speed and efficiency against a weaker arm like Hudson make him a vital component of our SB-focused strategy.\n\nWe are navigating a few situational variables that dictate our final configuration. The most difficult bench decision involved **Marcell Ozuna**, who was held out primarily due to the daunting presence of Brandon Woodruff; with the opposing xERA hovering near the 2.90 mark, the optimizer prioritized the higher floor provided by **Andy Pages** and **Heliot Ramos**. While **Heliot Ramos** provides a slight boost due to his speed and base-stealing potential, we are keeping a close eye on the 34% rain risk in the **Coby Mayo** matchup. **Coby Mayo** remains in the lineup for his park-driven potential, but if the weather turns, we have **Nolan Schanuel** on standby. We are also monitoring lineup confirmations for **Liam Hicks**, **Heliot Ramos**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Andy Pages**; should these projected batting orders shift downward, their efficiency scores will be re-evaluated to ensure we aren't burning game caps on suboptimal high-order spots.",
